NEW ENGLAND STEAMSHIP COMPANY, Libelant-Appellant, v. THE Steamer EXPRESS, Her Engines, etc., The Export Steamship Corporation, Claimant-Respondent-Appellee. No. 94. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Dec. 5, 1932. Haight, Smith, Griffin & Deming, of New York City (Henry M. Hewitt and James Mc-Kown, Jr., both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. *1037Kirlin, Campbell, Hiekox, Keating & MeGrann, of New York City (Robert S. Er-skine and Henry P. Elliott, both of New York City, of counsel), for S.'S. Express.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
